# 2026-06-03 22:53:22.601940
+
+Fix the analyze_product() function in tiktok-ugc-studio/gemini_agent.py:
+
+The MAIN PROBLEM: Image prompts are in English and too generic ("Holding the product naturally in hand"). The model OUTPUTS English prompts, but Flux doesn't know what the product looks like, so it generates wrong things (headphones → keyboard).
+
+SOLUTION: Change the system_prompt in analyze_product() to:
+1. Instruct the model to OUTPUT ALL prompts in THAI LANGUAGE only (ภาษาไทยเท่านั้น)
+2. Tell the model to DESCRIBE what the product LOOKS like in each prompt - color, shape, material, packaging details (based on the image the model can see)
+3. Generate hooks based on actual product pain points from the image analysis
+4. The image is passed as image_base64 parameter - the Mistral model can see it
+
+The current system_prompt has:
+- Research context passed as JSON (OK but not enough)
+- The example output is in English (WRONG - should be Thai)
+- The prompt doesn't force the model to describe product appearance in the image prompts
+
+Change example output format from English to Thai.
+Also fix _fallback_analysis to generate Thai content with product appearance.
+
+Key: Keep the same return JSON format keys: image_prompts (array of {id, name, prompt}), video_prompt, hook_suggestions, marketing_copy, hashtags
+But ALL string values must be in THAI language.
+
+The image_base64 IS passed to _call_mistral so the model CAN see the product - tell it to USE THAT VISUAL INFORMATION.
+

